### Use com REST Client (VS Code) ou JetBrains HTTP Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@entityId = 018e4a2c-6b4d-7000-9410-abcdef123456

# Authentication Headers (required if SERVICE_KEYS is configured)
# In dev mode (SERVICE_KEYS empty), these headers are optional
@serviceName = myservice
@serviceKey = sk_myservice_abc123

### ============================================
### Health Checks (Public - no auth required)
### ============================================

### Liveness Probe
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Readiness Probe (verifica conexão com DB)
GET {{baseUrl}}/ready

### ============================================
### Entities - CRUD (Protected - auth required)
### ============================================

### Criar Entity
POST {{baseUrl}}/entities
Content-Type: application/json
X-Service-Name: {{serviceName}}
X-Service-Key: {{serviceKey}}

{
  "name": "João da Silva",
  "email": "joao@example.com"
}

### Criar Entity (outro exemplo)
POST {{baseUrl}}/entities
Content-Type: application/json
X-Service-Name: {{serviceName}}
X-Service-Key: {{serviceKey}}

{
  "name": "Maria Santos",
  "email": "maria@example.com"
}

### Listar Entities (paginado)
GET {{baseUrl}}/entities?page=1&limit=20
X-Service-Name: {{serviceName}}
X-Service-Key: {{serviceKey}}

### Listar Entities (com filtros)
GET {{baseUrl}}/entities?name=maria&active_only=true&page=1&limit=20
X-Service-Name: {{serviceName}}
X-Service-Key: {{serviceKey}}

### Buscar Entity por ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/entities/{{entityId}}
X-Service-Name: {{serviceName}}
X-Service-Key: {{serviceKey}}

### Atualizar Entity
PUT {{baseUrl}}/entities/{{entityId}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-Service-Name: {{serviceName}}
X-Service-Key: {{serviceKey}}

{
  "name": "João da Silva Updated",
  "email": "joao.novo@example.com"
}

### Deletar Entity (Soft Delete)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/entities/{{entityId}}
X-Service-Name: {{serviceName}}
X-Service-Key: {{serviceKey}}

### ============================================
### Casos de Erro
### ============================================

### Email Inválido
POST {{baseUrl}}/entities
Content-Type: application/json
X-Service-Name: {{serviceName}}
X-Service-Key: {{serviceKey}}

{
  "name": "Teste Email",
  "email": "email-invalido"
}

### Entity não encontrada
GET {{baseUrl}}/entities/00000000-0000-7000-0000-000000000000
X-Service-Name: {{serviceName}}
X-Service-Key: {{serviceKey}}

### ============================================
### Com Idempotency Key (evita duplicação)
### ============================================

### Criar Entity com Idempotency Key
POST {{baseUrl}}/entities
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: unique-key-123
X-Service-Name: {{serviceName}}
X-Service-Key: {{serviceKey}}

{
  "name": "Entity Idempotente",
  "email": "idempotent@example.com"
}

### ============================================
### Casos de Erro de Autenticação
### ============================================

### Sem headers de auth (retorna 401 se SERVICE_KEYS configurada)
POST {{baseUrl}}/entities
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Sem Auth",
  "email": "noauth@example.com"
}

### Chave inválida (retorna 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/entities
Content-Type: application/json
X-Service-Name: {{serviceName}}
X-Service-Key: wrong_key

{
  "name": "Chave Errada",
  "email": "wrongkey@example.com"
}
